<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-110-680  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 110 680.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering  March 1989 v15 n3p314(12).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Detection of Ada static deadlocks using Petri net invariants.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Murata, Tadao; Shenker, Boris; Shatz, Sol M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A relatively efficient method for the detection of static(inconsistency and circular) deadlocks in ADA tasking programs isdeveloped which is based on the analysis of Petri net models.Themethod consists of: the translation of the ADA program into aPetri net model called an ADA net, which reveals thecommunications patterns and control flow of the program; thedetection and removal of inconsistency deadlocks; and thedetection and removal of circular deadlocks.andP;  Structural anddynamic analysis techniques are used to analyze the ADA nets.andO;Algorithms for the detection of the two classes of deadlocks aredeveloped.andP;  The algorithms use Petri net invariants to minimizethe the computational complexities of the process.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Research and DevelopmentADADeadlock Detection and RecoveryNew TechniqueSystem DesignSpecificationsSystem Development.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Stepwise translation of an Ada program into an Ada net. (chart)Process-subnets in a distributed environment. (chart)Overview of the static deadlock detection method. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>